        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="KR3a0014-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:10:25.062+09:00">Master Wenzhong’s teaching</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:10:36.266+09:00">is the continuation of the Way of theUncrowned King [i.e. Confucius];</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:10:50.629+09:00">therefore, the chapter “The KinglyWay” (Wangdao pian 王道篇) is placed at the head of this work.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:11:06.811+09:00">Formersage kings of antiquity</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:11:52.605+09:00">observed attentively the movements of the TwoModes to make certain that [these movements] were in accord with thepower of heaven and earth;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:11:42.237+09:00"> therefore, the chapter “Heaven and Earth”(Tian di pian 天地篇) follows next.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:12:52.064+09:00">When heaven is observed as thesuperior and earth the subordinate,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:13:03.619+09:00">then [the relationship between] thesovereign and the vassal will be [properly] established;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:13:14.696+09:00">therefore, thechapter “Service to the Sovereign” (Shijun pian 事君篇) follows next.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:14:06.09+09:00">When serving the sovereign,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:14:18.382+09:00">no one adhered more closely to heavenlypatterns than the Duke of Zhou;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:14:46.457+09:00">therefore, the chapter “Duke of Zhou”(Zhou gong pian 周公篇) follows next.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:14:55.245+09:00">The Way of Duke of Zhou</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:15:15.96+09:00">isnuminous because it adheres to The Book of Changes at its core;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:15:27.622+09:00">therefore,the chapter “Queries about the Changes” (Wen Yi pian 問易篇) followsnext.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:15:51.668+09:00">The Changes</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:16:06.643+09:00"> is the fount of transformation,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:16:18.197+09:00">but nothing ismore effective than the transformation of cultural practices by means ofrites and music;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:17:45.269+09:00">therefore, the chapter “Rites and Music” (Li yue pian 禮樂篇) follows next.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:17:58.566+09:00">Rites and music amplify culture while chroniclesrecord it;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:18:09.853+09:00">therefore, the chapter “Delineating History” (Shushi pian 述史篇) follows next.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:18:16.388+09:00">To promote refined culture and establish institutionalstandards,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:18:41.884+09:00">there is nothing more effective than to elucidate the principlesof things.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:18:51.586+09:00">Wei Xiang had accomplished exactly that;4</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:19:00.517+09:00">therefore, the chapter“Wei Xiang” (Wei Xiang pian 魏相篇) follows next.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:19:08.63+09:00">When the yin andthe yang forces are harmonized,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:19:51.924+09:00">then we will see clearly the innate patternsof things and the law of nature.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:20:38.437+09:00">When we have investigated exhaustivelythe innate patterns of things and explored thoroughly the law ofnature, then we will arrive at an understanding of the concept ofmandates;5</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:20:28.796+09:00"> therefore, the chapter “Determining Mandates” (Liming pian立命篇) follows next.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:21:16.587+09:00">Without the Book of Changes, how can we everapprehend the law of nature and the workings of mandates?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:21:44.696+09:00">Mr. Guan</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:21:52.124+09:00">isthe one who achieved the most profound understanding of the Changes;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_011-2a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:21:53.39+09:00">therefore, the chapter “Guan Lang” (Guan Lang pian 關朗篇) followsnext to conclude this work.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-34a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:26:07.108+09:00">When the Master gained Cheng, Qiu, Dong and Xue [as his students], hisSix [Continued] Classics became more luminous.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-34a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:27:00.415+09:00">The compilation of theDuiwen (The Dialogues)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-34a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:28:15.338+09:00">was the effort of these four students.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-34a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:28:26.068+09:00">But first,Dong and Qiu died prematurely;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-34a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:28:36.527+09:00">next, Cheng and Xue also passed away.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-34a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:28:59.285+09:00">How could Master Wenzhong’s teaching flourish?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-34a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:30:59.69+09:00">Alas,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-34a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:31:32.762+09:00">we must nowawait the coming of a savant!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:49:12.333+09:00">To discuss literary refinement without addressing internal integrity,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:49:34.266+09:00">this means that culture (wen) no longer exists in the world.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:49:56.697+09:00">How isthe Kingly Way going to prosper?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-48a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:59:23.037+09:00">Master Wenzhong said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-48a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:59:29.867+09:00">A strong state conquers others with militaryforce.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-48a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:59:34.748+09:00">A state possessing hegemonic power conquers others with wisestrategies.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-48a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:59:45.554+09:00">A state possessing monarchial power conquers others with thedictates of what is appropriate.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-48a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T01:59:56.618+09:00">A state possessing imperial power conquersothers with its moral influence.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-48a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:04:45.591+09:00">To be sure, the imperial system has long ceased to exist but in name only.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-48a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:02:24.47+09:00">A state possessing supreme powerconquers others by inaction.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-48a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:02:24.471+09:00">he cannot possibly defeat the ways of monarchy andhegemony.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-48a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:02:24.471+09:00">If the Son of Heaven employs military forceto conquer others,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-48a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:02:24.625+09:00">On what basis then can he take the name emperor for himself?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-4a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:06:02.803+09:00">Master Wenzhong said,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-4a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:06:09.873+09:00">“It has been a long time since there was anemperor who conducted himself as an emperor should.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-4a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:06:13.02+09:00">Wang Xiaoyi asked,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-4a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:06:23.28+09:00">“Why then do you still use the term ‘emperor’ inYuanjing [when you refer to the rulers of past dynasties]?”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-4a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:06:25.876+09:00">The Master said,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-4a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:06:32.865+09:00">“If you want to rectify names and validate actuality,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-4a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:06:37.51+09:00">you cannot abandon using this term.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-4a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:06:45.95+09:00">For those who functioned as emperorsin the past dynasties,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-4a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:06:46.433+09:00">they did so in name only.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:08:02.493+09:00">The Master said,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:08:07.377+09:00">“When the states of the Central Plains deviate from theproper way,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:08:14.497+09:00">the neighboring barbarian tribes all know it.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:08:18.408+09:00">Wei Zheng said,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:08:29.646+09:00">“Would you please elaborate on this?”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:08:34.643+09:00">The Master said,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:08:44.984+09:00">“‘When the Lesser Elegantiae falls into complete disuse,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:08:49.75+09:00">all the neighboring barbarian tribes begin to cause disturbances onthe frontier.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:08:57.918+09:00">This indicates that the states of the Central Plains had deviatedfrom the proper way.’5</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:09:04.464+09:00">Isn’t that the explanation?”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:09:10.735+09:00">When Wei Zheng withdrew, he said to Xue Shou,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_010-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:09:11.148+09:00">“I now know what isthe state of our time’s affairs.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_004-55a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:11:12.879+09:00">Zheng He slandered the Master in front of the Duke of Yue, saying,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_004-55a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:11:22.887+09:00">“It washe [i.e., Wang Tong] who treated the Duke with disrespect.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_004-55a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:11:30.778+09:00">Why does theDuke still hold him in esteem?”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_004-55a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:11:45.315+09:00">The Duke of Yue sent someone to ask theMaster about this.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_004-55a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:11:50.194+09:00">The Master said,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_004-55a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:12:20.867+09:00">“If the Duke may be treated with disrespect,then I have acted correctly. If the Duke may not be treated withdisrespect, then I have erred. In either case, it reflects on me. Why doesthe Duke make it his business?” Thereupon, the Duke continued to treathim with the same regard as he did before.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-28a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:15:03.89+09:00">Whenever the Master saw a farmer tilling, he always paid him respect byinquiring of his welfare.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-28a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:15:17.345+09:00">Whenever he saw an official from court, healways paid him respect by bowing his head.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-28a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:15:29.696+09:00">So long as he was within theboundary of a village or neighborhood,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-28a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:16:05.413+09:00">Everymorning,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_005-28a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:16:13.226+09:00">he washed and dressed himself as soon as the rooster crowed.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-34a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:18:15.168+09:00">Shutian said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-34a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:18:31.539+09:00">Master Wenzhong’s teaching has risen</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-34a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:19:20.258+09:00"> just as the Sui hascome to its final years</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-34a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:19:24.848+09:00">and the royal house is reaching its final end.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-34a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:19:32.328+09:00">Forthose who are facing ruin,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-34a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:19:39.738+09:00">I lament that he did not get to apply [his talentto save them].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-34a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:19:44.432+09:00">For those who are about to prosper,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-34a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:19:49.271+09:00">I regret that he did notget to see [it happen].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-34a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:19:56.202+09:00">How assiduously he applied himself!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-34a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:19:59.571+09:00">How soundhis words were!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-34a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T02:20:00.738+09:00">How devoted he was to the welfare of the people!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:43:49.075+09:00">When the Master was in Chang’an,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:43:56.464+09:00">Yang Su, Su Kui and Li Delin all askedfor a meeting with him.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:44:03.2+09:00">The Master went and talked to them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:44:10.778+09:00">When hereturned, he appeared distressed.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:44:23.436+09:00">The disciples asked him the cause ofhis distress.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:45:04.172+09:00">The Master said,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:45:28.192+09:00">“When Yang Su talked to me,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:45:35.757+09:00">he spent all day discussingstatecraft (zheng) without addressing the transformation of people(hua).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:45:45.512+09:00">When Su Kui talked to me,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:45:49.565+09:00">he spent all day discussing tonal qualities(sheng) without addressing correct measures (ya).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:46:02.705+09:00">When Li Delintalked to me, he spent all day</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-16a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:46:03.116+09:00">discussing literary refinement (wen) withoutaddressing internal integrity (li).”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:47:04.057+09:00">The disciples asked,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:47:09.053+09:00">“Why should that distress you?”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:47:31.014+09:00">The Master said,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:47:40.812+09:00">“You don’t understand.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:47:45.694+09:00"> The three of them are all advisorsto the court on policy matters.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:47:53.753+09:00">Now, to discuss statecraft withoutaddressing the transformation of people,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:47:58.584+09:00">this means that ritual (li) nolonger exists in the world.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:48:12.248+09:00">To discuss tonal qualities without addressingcorrect measures,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:48:54.688+09:00">this means that music (yue) no longer exists in theworld.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:50:06.752+09:00">That is why I am distressed.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:50:53.033+09:00">The disciples withdrew. The Master took out his zither and played thesong suite “Mighty” [from the Book of Songs]. </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-17a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:53:54.875+09:00">The disciples were allmoved to tears by his music.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-21a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:57:50.728+09:00">The Duke of Yue asked about government.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-21a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:58:29.995+09:00">The master said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-21a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:58:35.017+09:00"> “Be respectfuland frugal.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-21a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:58:39.507+09:00">The Duke of Pi asked about government.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-21a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:58:45.78+09:00">The Master said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-21a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:58:48.833+09:00"> “Bepure and fair.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-21a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:59:02.264+09:00">The Duke of Anping asked about government.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-21a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:59:13.485+09:00">The Mastersaid:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_006-21a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T03:59:13.779+09:00">“Do not be bellicose for the sake of fame.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:06:40.536+09:00">The Master said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:06:48.623+09:00">[Yao] Yi is pure and decorous.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:07:00.284+09:00"> {[Li] Jing is clement butdecisive.}</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:07:06.127+09:00">[Dou] Wei is congenial and learned.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:07:10.704+09:00">[Xue] Shou is untrammeledin deportment but serious in mind.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:07:15.534+09:00"> [Jia] Qiong is perspicaciousand resolute.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:07:21.724+09:00">[Du] Yan is honest and uncompromising.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:07:27.994+09:00">{[Fang] Xuanlingis astute but circumspect.42</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:07:37.375+09:00">[Wei] Zheng is forthright but compliant.}</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:07:40.95+09:00">[Wen] Daya is forbearing and magnanimous.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:07:45.234+09:00"> [Chen] Shuda has attainedsimplicity and equilibrium.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:07:53.438+09:00">If they meet the opportune time,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:08:08.869+09:00">they willrise to ranks no lower than chief ministers and grand councilors.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-3a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:08:09.965+09:00">Even so,they have not yet perfected their knowledge on rites and music.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-23a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:11:43.042+09:00">Wen Daya asked: “What must a person be like before he can be trusted togovern others?”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-23a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:12:02.692+09:00">The Master said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-23a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:12:15.722+09:00">“He must act by the principle of humaneness,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-23a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:12:24.399+09:00">live bythe principle of tolerance,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-23a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:12:39.843+09:00">and he must have a deep understanding of theintent of rites and music.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-23a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:12:55.251+09:00">[Wen Daya] asked: “May I ask what kind of a person would rank next?”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-23a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:13:06.286+09:00">The Master said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-23a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:13:32.424+09:00">“He must be true in words</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-23a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:13:42.115+09:00"> and considerate in action.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-23a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:13:51.455+09:00">He must not be moved even when he is tempted with benefit or threatenedwith harm.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-24a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:13:57.705+09:00">[Wen Daya] asked again:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-24a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:15:03.211+09:00">The Master said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-24a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:15:08.048+09:00">“He must be respectful but unyielding,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-24a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:15:13.989+09:00">incorruptiblebut mindful.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-24a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:15:23.815+09:00">He must be circumspect in order to preserve himself.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-24a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:15:43.725+09:00">Butsuch a person is not good enough to rise above others.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-24a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:15:58.732+09:00">The Master said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-24a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:16:10.936+09:00">“Any person doing less than this</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-24a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:16:20.02+09:00">would be no different than a thief.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-24a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:16:36.709+09:00"> If must be, he might beenrolled among the reserve staff, perhaps.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_007-24a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:16:55.099+09:00">Howcan he be trusted with government affairs?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-50a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:19:28.274+09:00">The deviation of historical writing [from its proper function]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-50a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:19:32.737+09:00">began with[Sima] Qian and [Ban] Gu.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-50a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:19:44.122+09:00">What they recorded was elaborate; but, of alltheir intents and purposes, it was inadequate.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-50a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:19:52.658+09:00">The misrepresentation ofthe Spring and Autumn Annals</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-50a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:20:09.206+09:00">began with [Liu] Xin [46 BC–AD 23] and[Liu] Xiang [ca. 79–8 BC].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_002-50a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:20:11.845+09:00">They disregarded the original text and reliedonly on its commentaries.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-11a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:23:00.528+09:00">“May I ask why the Continued Songs encompasses theentire repertoire of the Six Dynasties era?”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-11a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:22:49.962+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-11a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:23:12.916+09:00">The Master said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-11a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:23:29.8+09:00">“I presumethat you ask because Zhongni’s [i.e. Confucius’s] Three Hundred Songs[i.e., Book of Songs] begins and ends with the Zhou era.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-11a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:23:38.539+09:00">Xue Shou said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-11a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:23:42.287+09:00">“Yes.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-11a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:23:46.36+09:00">The Master said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-11a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:23:50.972+09:00">“How dare I ever expect to be Zhongni’s equal?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-11a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:24:08.452+09:00">Yetat such a time of vicissitudes,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-11a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:24:14.337+09:00">I have to keep looking up to him.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-11a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:24:34.58+09:00">That iswhy I begin and end [the Continued Songs] with the Six Dynasties era.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-11a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:25:42.021+09:00">It is for the sake of instructing [the generation of our time].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-36a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:26:50.015+09:00">Heaven and Earth may have created me,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-36a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:26:54.223+09:00">but they cannot nurture me.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-36a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:27:01.071+09:00">Myparents may have nurtured me,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-36a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:27:07.807+09:00">but they cannot help me to achieve perfection.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-36a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:27:13.756+09:00">The one who helped me to achieve perfection is the Master [i.e.,Confucius].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-36a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:27:26.836+09:00">[The power of] the Way is not only manifested in [the benevolenceI owe to] Heaven and Earth or my parents.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-36a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:27:41.21+09:00">I, Tong, am beholden tothe Master for the benevolence</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-36a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:27:48.951+09:00">that he bestowed on me as much as I amto my own parents.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3a0014_tls_001-36a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-01-13T04:28:14.492+09:00">Are you, my lad, confusing the proper relationships ofhumankind?</seg>
                </p>
